modules.description: Implements HTTP/2 server connections over Lwt, handling requests and errors on provided sockets. Works with H2 streams, requests, and responses, using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. Used to serve HTTP/2 endpoints by binding to a socket and processing incoming connections with custom request and error handlers.

This module manages HTTP/2 client connections over a provided socket, enabling asynchronous request-response interactions. It supports sending requests with optional trailers, handling server-initiated pushes, and managing connection lifecycle operations like shutdown and ping. Concrete use cases include implementing HTTP/2-based APIs, streaming data from a server, and handling bidirectional communication over a secure socket.

Implements HTTP/2 server and client connections over Lwt for asynchronous I/O. Handles streams, requests, and responses on sockets with custom handlers for serving endpoints or making client requests. Used to build HTTP/2 services that process incoming connections, send client requests with trailers, and manage bidirectional communication securely.
